    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02312.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">113 east 10th street</name>
                    <name type="place">near 3d Avenue</name>
                    <name type="place">New York</name>
                    <date when="1877-03-08">Thursday noon March 8<ptr target="loc.02312_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Miss Hillard</salute></opener>

            <p>Come by all means&#8212;I shall be in at 8 p m Saturday, expecting you&#8212;&amp; failing then (any thing preventing you) shall be in at 11 a m on Sunday&#8212;</p>
            <p>If you come Saturday afternoon we will promise not to make <hi rend="underline">company</hi> of you&#8212;Mrs. Johnston &amp; all will be delighted to receive you too&#8212;(&amp; you shall have a cup of tea &amp; a biscuit to refresh)&#8212;Come&#8212;</p>


            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
